sentences: One of biggest moments of Randa's career was performing at the Auckland Big Day Out 2014.
In 2018, Randa was featured on an Air New Zealand safety video alongside Julian Dennison, Kings and Theia.
It is the 18th of Air New Zealand's safety videos, which started in 2009.
Randa started making music while living briefly in Sydney, Australia, in 2011.
2013 RIANZ New Zealand Music Awards – Best Music Video - Frankenstein (Nominated)
2014 RIANZ New Zealand Music Awards – Critics’ Choice prize (Winner)
2019 RIANZ New Zealand Music Awards – Best Music Video - Rock Bottom (Winner)
Randa is best known for their song "Rangers", which is used on a TV health promotion ad in New Zealand called "Go the distance".
One of biggest moments of Randa's career was performing at the Auckland Big Day Out 2014.
The video took nine days to record, shooting all across New Zealand.
The video was dumped by Air New Zealand after only three months due to public criticism.
Randa was educated at Carmel College, Auckland, for their high school years.
